                    "@type": "Answer",
                    text: "Primary issues include intake manifold runner flap failure (especially pre-2014), VVT actuator sticking, throttle body carbon buildup, and coolant leaks from the thermostat housing. These are documented in Land Rover service bulletins. Using incorrect oil or extended service intervals accelerates wear. Coolant chemistry and fuel quality are critical factors in longevity.",
